<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   NAM Foreign Ministers Hold Sideline Meetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NAM Foreign Ministers Hold Sideline Meetings </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Egypt's Musa, Iran's Velayati Meet </H4>

<F P=102> NC0206093994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0840 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 Jun (MENA) -- [Egyptian] Foreign Minister 
'Amr Musa met this morning with his Iranian counterpart, 'Ali 
Akbar Velayati, on the sidelines of the Non-Aligned Movement 
[NAM] Conference. 
  Velayati described the one-hour meeting as extremely 
constructive and positive and said that NAM and international 
cooperation issues were discussed. 
  In a statement he made following the meeting, Velayati added 
that Egypt and Iran expressed their desire for constructive 
bilateral cooperation in the international arena, NAM, and the 
Islamic Conference Organization. He said that he and Musa 
discussed various issues, including the situations in Yemen and 
Bosnia and regional matters. 
  Velayati refused to answer questions on bilateral issues 
between Egypt and Iran or on the criticism by British Foreign 
Office Minister Douglas Hurd that Iran is sponsoring terrorism. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

