<H3> <TI>   NAM Foreign Ministers Hold Sideline Meetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NAM Foreign Ministers Hold Sideline Meetings </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Velayati Meets With Bahrain's Al Khalifah </H4>

<F P=102> LD0106200394 Tehran IRNA in English 1818 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0106200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, June 1, IRNA -- Iran's Foreign Minister 
'Ali-Akbar Velayati and Foreign Minister of Bahrain Shaykh 
Muhammad Bin-Mubarak al Khalifah here Wednesday [1 June] 
conferred on topics of mutual interest and on how to broaden 
relations between the two countries. 
  Al Khalifah said his government would exert every effort to 
further develop the relations between the two Persian Gulf 
countries. 
  He said Iran and Bahrain have identical views on many 
important issues including those brought up at the current 11th 
assembly of foreign ministers of the non-aligned nations. 
  Velayati, too, said his talks with his Bahraini ounterpart 
were very friendly. 
  He added that the two countries have common positions 
towards 
many regional and international issues including those of Yemen 
and Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

