<H3> <TI>   NAM Foreign Ministers Hold Sideline Meetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NAM Foreign Ministers Hold Sideline Meetings </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Syria's al-Shar' Meets Yemeni, Cuban Minister </H4>

<F P=102> JN0206075094 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 0415 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0206075094 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo -- [Syrian] Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' 
resumed his meetings yesterday on the sidelines of the 11th 
Non-Aligned Foreign Ministers' Conference. 
  Al-Shar' met with Yemeni Foreign Minister Muhammad 
Basindwah. 
They exchanged views on the latest developments in the situation 
in Yemen. 
  Al-Shar' also met with Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto 
Robaina. The talks dealt with relations between the two friendly 
countries, and the need to reactivate the Non-Aligned Movement's 
role in light of international changes. 
  Al-Shar' also met with Iranian Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar 
Velayati. The talks dealt with the situation in the region, the 
latest developments in the peace process, and bilateral 
relations. 
  The foreign minister also met with (Pavel Tratinka), 
assistant to the Czech foreign minister. 
  During the meeting, the talks dealt with bilateral relations 
and developments in the Middle East peace process. 

</TEXT>

