<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   NAM Foreign Ministers Hold Sideline Meetings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NAM Foreign Ministers Hold Sideline Meetings </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Al-Sahhaf Talks With Venezuelan Counterpart </H4>

<F P=102> JN3005141294 Baghdad INA in English 1145 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3005141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, May 30, INA -- Foreign minister, chairman of 
the Iraqi delegation to the Non-Aligned conference, Muhammad 
Sa'id al-Sahhaf today conferred in Cairo with his Venezuelan 
counterpart Burelli Rivas. 
  During the meeting, Mr. al-Sahhaf briefed the Venezuelan 
official on developments of relation between Iraq and the 
Security Council and the U.N. special commission and Iraq's 
implementation of its reciprocal commitments pursuant to the 
Security Council Resolutions. 
  He also explained Iraq's assessment of the positive 
discussions by the Security Council members during the recent 
session of the Council held in New York, confirming that Iraq 
demands the next routine review must be decisive as for lifting 
the blockade imposed on the country since August 1990. 
  INA Cairo correspondent said that the Iraqi and Venezuelan 
ministers had also discussed bilateral ties and means of 
resuming them. 
  They also exchanged view points on a package of regional and 
global issues of common concern. 
  Present at the meeting were Iraq's Foreign Undersecretary 
Wisam al-Zahawi and Iraq's Arab League Permanent Delegate Dr 
Nabil Najim. 

</TEXT>

