<H3> <TI>   Rabin Dismisses 'Arafat's Remarks on Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Dismisses 'Arafat's Remarks on Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0106182294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 1 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0106182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister has dismissed Yasir 'Arafat's 
remarks that Jerusalem is the capital of Palestine. Mr. Rabin 
reacted to 'Arafat's remarks today, saying: He can talk. In a 
meeting of leaders of the Jewish National Fund at the Hyatt 
Hotel in Jerusalem Rabin stated: I heard that somebody in Tunis 
said something; I would like to declare here that united 
Jerusalem is the capital of the Jews and so it will remain 
forever. Our correspondent Esti Peres reported the prime 
minister's remarks. 

</TEXT>

