<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Settlers Organize To Prevent 'Arafat's Arrival </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Settlers Organize To Prevent 'Arafat's Arrival </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0106181794 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in 
Hebrew 1700 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0106181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Rina Matzliah] </F>
  [Text] Our correspondent Rina Matzliah has learned the 
details of a secret plan drawn up by the settlers in the 
territories, under which they will try to take over two points 
within the autonomy area in Jericho and hold onto them in an 
attempt to foil the arrival of PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat. Our 
correspondent reports from the place where the settlers have 
convened: 
  [Begin Matzliah recording] The heads of the Council of 
Jewish Settlements in Judaea, Samaria, and Gaza rented a 
particularly large hall for a particularly large convention in 
which their protest activities for the coming days are being 
presented. Jerusalem and Jericho are the two centers of these 
protest activities. In Jericho the settlers plan to take 
control of two Jewish points: the Na'aran synagogue which, 
contrary to its name, is not located near Kibbutz Na'aran but 
rather inside the autonomy area, and the Hasmonean Palace which 
is also located inside the autonomy area. The settlers intend 
to take control of these two points, to establish facts on the 
ground, and to remain there, as was the case with the ancient 
synagogue in Jericho. 
  A large-scale protest is planned for Jerusalem too. The 
heads of the council are negotiating with businessmen in 
Jerusalem in an attempt to stage a general strike there on the 
day Yasir 'Arafat arrives in the area. Most importantly, do not 
dare let the PLO leader climb Temple Mount. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

