<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Cease Funding for Gaza `Busywork' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Cease Funding for Gaza `Busywork' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3005171094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 30 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3005171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the wake of the implementation of the autonomy 
agreement, Israel will stop financing busywork jobs for 
Palestinians in the Gaza Strip. Security sources noted that in 
May Israel employed 18,000 Gazans in busywork jobs at a cost of 
20 million shekels. Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that 
Faysal al-Husayni announced that the Palestinians would shortly 
have enough money to finance the expenses stemming from the 
implementation of the Gaza- Jericho agreement. 
  The Agriculture Ministry will immediately proceed to set up 
a 
special unit to oversee the passage of produce from the autonomy 
to Israel. The unit will tighten controls on shipments of 
produce from the territories to the ultra-Orthodox community. 
Our correspondent Shulamit Schmerling reports that the decision 
to establish the unit already at this point was made at a 
special meeting with the agriculture minister in a bid to curb 
the smuggling of produce by taking advantage of the permits 
given to the ultra-Orthodox community which is currently 
observing a ritual fallow year. Originally, the unit was 
scheduled to be established only after the opening of the 
borders with the autonomy to the passage of produce. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

