<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Free Agricultural Imports From Autonomy Delayed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Free Agricultural Imports From Autonomy Delayed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2805112594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 28 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2805112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Agriculture Minister Ya'aqov Tzur has decided to 
delay the opening of Israel's borders for free passage of 
agricultural produce from the autonomy until satisfactory 
compensation is provided to Israeli farmers. 
  According to the agreement, the borders were to open this 
week for free passage of fruit, vegetables, cattle, and flocks 
-- apart from poultry -- eggs, tomatoes, cucumbers, and 
potatoes, which will gradually be allowed in under quotas. The 
Ministry of Agriculture is to approve the import of vegetables 
from the Gaza Strip into Israel in a few days time. Tests show 
there is no danger in the vegetables and the farmers there do 
not use pesticides. Agriculture Minister Ya'aqov Tzur is to 
instruct the ministry to publish all information concerning 
laboratory tests on agricultural produce as of tomorrow. 
Recently, tests of fruit and vegetables showed the remnants of 
dangerous pesticides have been found in several Israeli 
agricultural products. The contaminated produce was destroyed 
and the farmers were fined. 

</TEXT>

