<H3> <TI>   Group Claims Restrictions Violate Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Group Claims Restrictions Violate Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0206104694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 2 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0206104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The organization Peace Watch claims that Israel has 
violated the autonomy agreement signed in Cairo by limiting the 
entry of agricultural products from Gaza into Israel. The 
independent watch-dog group said the eighth paragraph in the 
fourth appendix calls for free passage to markets. 
  Israel has limited the entrance of agricultural products 
from 
the autonomous area until proper compensation is arranged for 
Israeli producers and until quality control for agricultural 
products and livestock are ensured. A joint Israeli-Palestinian 
committee has been set up to deal with the matter. 

</TEXT>

