<H3> <TI>   Labor MK Efrayim Sne Appointed Health Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor MK Efrayim Sne Appointed Health Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2905145294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 29 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2905145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Labor Central Committee approved by a decisive 
majority the appointment of Knesset Member [MK] Efrayim Sne as 
health minister. Prime Minister Rabin said that in view of the 
difficult situation, Israel needs a full-time health minister. 
There is nobody to talk to in the Histadrut Labor Federation and 
its Kupat Holim health fund is bankrupt. Mr. Rabin said the two 
other ministerial portfolios are being saved for SHAS [Torah 
Observing Sephardim]. Our correspondent Shmu'el Tal reports 
that a minister without portfolio, either Yosi Beilin or MK 
Avraham Burg, is also expected to be appointed. 
  MK Sne thanked the Central Committee for its support and 
called on Kupat Holim Director General Avigdor Kaplan to remain 
in his post and participate in the efforts to rehabilitate the 
fund. 

</TEXT>

