<H3> <TI>   Al-Turabi Said Involved in Triggering Yemeni War </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Turabi Said Involved in Triggering Yemeni War </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0106145494 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 29 May 94 p 9 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Brothers" page] </F>
  [Text] Informed Sudanese sources have affirmed that Dr. 
Hasan al-Turabi [leader of the National Islamic Front] is 
personally involved in triggering the civil war in Yemen. The 
same sources say that some time ago al-Turabi met with 
'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani, a representative of the Islamic Reform 
Group; and 'Abd-al-'Aziz Yasin, a representative of the Muslim 
Brotherhood in Yemen. He persuaded them to reject the Pledge 
and Agreement Document signed by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid in Jordan. 
  The sources note that al-Turabi claimed to some Yemeni 
forces 
that the continuing political crisis in Yemen will eventually 
lead those he called "the Islamic forces" to control power both 
in northern and southern Yemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

