<H3> <TI>   `Terrorist Elements' Reportedly Granted Passports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Terrorist Elements' Reportedly Granted Passports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0106142994 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 29 May 94 p 9 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Brothers" page] </F>
  [Text] Informed sources in the Sudanese capital have 
affirmed that during the first week of March the Sudanese 
Interior Ministry granted Sudanese nationality and Sudanese 
passports to more than 120 Arab refugees from Egypt, Algeria, 
Tunis, Jordan, Libya and Palestine, in implementation of the 
recommendations of the Arab Islamic Popular Conference, which is 
chaired by National Islamic Front leader Dr. Hasan al-Turabi. 
  The Islamic Movements's department at the Revolution's 
Security Agency will keep files on these terrorist elements and 
will follow up on the settlement, accommodation, and guarding of 
these elements, who are in camps throughout Sudan. 

</TEXT>

