<F P=103> NC0106184094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, June 1 (MENA)--Sudanese security authorities 
have launched a large-scale arrest campaign against leaderships 
and activists of the opposition Ummah Party. 
  The arrests, carried out on May 19, included a number of 
former ministers and key officials as well as university 
professors who are affiliated with the Ummah Party, according to 
a statement faxed to MENA today. 
  Families of the detainees were denied access to information 
on their whereabouts, the statement added. 

