<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir Returns From Austria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bashir Returns From Austria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0106162394 Khartoum SUNA in French 0940 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0106162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President 'Umar al-Bashir returned to Khartoum 
from Vienna yesterday afternoon [31 May] at the end of a two-day 
visit to Austria at the invitation of President Thomas Kestil. 
In his arrival speech, General al-Bashir said he held several 
meetings in Vienna with Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni. At 
some of these meetings, which were behind closed doors, the two 
leaders discussed the development of bilateral relations. 
According to President al-Bashir, these meetings were aimed at 
improving relations between the two countries, given Uganda's 
important role in the Intergovernmental Authority on Drought and 
Development initiative on restoring peace to southern Sudan. He 
said the two sides agreed to strengthen ties to serve the 
interests of both peoples. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

