<F P=100> EGYPT </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Withdraws From National Dialogue Committee </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Withdraws From National Dialogue Committee </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Nasirite Party Suspends Participation </H4>

<F P=102> NC0106194894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1850 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Jun (MENA)--The Nasirite Arab Democratic 
Party announced a freeze on its participation in the committee 
in charge of preparation for national dialogue. 
  In a statement today, the party announced a freeze on its 
participation in the dialogue until the approach to this 
dialogue, its topics, and the parties involved in it are 
reviewed. The statement said that the committee in charge of 
preparing for the dialogue was formed in full violation of the 
agreement reached among the political parties. According to the 
statement, the committee was supposed to be formed after 
consultations among political parties and not by a National 
Democratic Party decision. 

</TEXT>

