<F P=100> EGYPT </F>
<H3> <TI>   Debt Service in Budget To Exceed 21 Billion Pounds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Debt Service in Budget To Exceed 21 Billion Pounds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0106131994 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 29 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-WAFD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Dr. Muhammad al-Razzaz has stated 
that 21.446 billion pounds will be earmarked for servicing the 
internal and external debts in the new budget, which will begin 
on 1 July. Dr. al-Razzaz pointed out that the treasury bills 
make up most of the internal debts owed by the government. He 
stressed the importance of the treasury bills in streamlining 
the budget deficit and absorbing the surplus in the country, 
whether from individuals or banks, to reduce inflation. The 
minister also stressed the importance of the treasury bills in 
stopping the drop in interest rates on savings in Egyptian 
pounds and in maintaining the rates of exchange. 
  Dr. al-Razzaz added that the state is spending 1.5 billion 
pounds to adjust the financial structure of the Egyptian railway 
and 220 millions to extend electricity to the countryside. 

</TEXT>

