<H3> <TI>   Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Arrives for Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Arrives for Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Comments on Yemeni Crisis </H4>

<F P=102> LD2705221794 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 2045 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705221794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kuwait, 27 May -- China has called on rival 
parties in Yemen to halt the fighting and resort to dialogue in 
order to solve the crisis there through peaceful means. 
  In a statement to KUNA on his arrival in Kuwait today at the 
beginning of a tour of several Arab countries, Tian Zengpei, the 
Chinese vice foreign minister, said that China was following 
with interest the development of the situation in Yemen and 
wished for a halt of the hostilities there. 
  The Chinese minister, whose country is a permanent member of 
the UN Security Council, said that the Yemeni crisis should be 
solved through peaceful means in order to preserve the interests 
of the Yemeni people. 
  The Chinese call comes at a time the UN Security Council 
members are trying to discuss the Yemeni crisis that entered its 
fourth week after fighting broke out between northern and 
southern troops on 4 May. [passage omitted] 
  The Chinese official said that he was carrying a written 
message from Chinese President Jiang Zemin to the Amir of Kuwait. 
  He added that, during his three-day visit to Kuwait, he will 
meet a number of Kuwaiti officials at the Foreign Affairs 
Ministry to discuss bilateral relations and issues of common 
interests. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

