BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kuwait, 28 May (KUNA) -- Visiting Chinese Deputy 
Foreign Minister Tian Zengpei met here today with Shaykh Sabah 
al-Ahmad, Kuwaiti first deputy prime minister and foreign 
minister. An official source at the Foreign Ministry told the 
Kuwaiti News Agency that Shaykh Sabah al-Ahmad has praised 
China's principled stance regarding the treacherous Iraqi 
aggression against Kuwait in August 1990. Shaykh Sabah 
al-Ahmad has also praised China's understanding of the need for 
the Iraqi regime's commitment to the implementation of 
legitimate international resolutions. 
  The source said that Shaykh Sabah al-Ahmad has noted 
Kuwait's 
stance regarding the need to compel Iraq to implement all the 
international resolutions pertaining to the war of liberation 
against Kuwait, stressing that the UN sanctions imposed on the 
Iraqi regime were the only guarantee to achieve this goal. 
[passage omitted] 
  The Chinese deputy foreign minister is visiting Kuwait at 
the 
start of a tour of a number of Arab countries. He is due to 
meet the amir tomorrow and deliver a message from Chinese 
President Jiang Zemin. 

</TEXT>

