<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aden Reports `Failed' Missile Attack on Refinery </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Reports `Failed' Missile Attack on Refinery </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0106152394 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1310 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0106152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1310 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the "Armed Forces Command of the </F>
Democratic Republic of Yemen"; place and date not given] 
  [Text] In the context of the escalation in the military 
situation and in an open challenge leveled against all the Arab 
and international efforts aimed to bring about an end to the 
fighting in Yemen, the al-Ahmar gang in Sanaa has launched 
missile and air strikes against the residential quarters and 
vital civil installations in Aden. Yesterday at dawn, Aden came 
under a missile attack aimed at civilian residential quarters. 
The missiles were engaged by our air defenses, which shot down 
one of the missiles in flight while another missile fell into 
the sea. This morning two enemy aircraft tried to bomb the 
little Aden refinery, one of the vital and important economic 
installations belonging to our Yemeni people. Our air defenses 
succeeded in foiling this treacherous attempt, which failed to 
achieve its objectives. However, one of the houses of the 
innocent citizens in little Aden was hit, killing a number of 
women and children. The Command of the Armed Forces in the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen, while condemning these barbarous 
acts which violate all the rules of war, reserves the right to 
respond strongly and decisively to this kind of aggression. Let 
those who are warned take heed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

