<H3> <TI>   Aden Reports `Heavy Losses' Inflicted on North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Reports `Heavy Losses' Inflicted on North </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0106194194 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1700 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0106194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1700 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by a "responsible source at the Command of the </F>
Armed Forces of the Democratic Republic of Yemen"; date not 
given] 
  [Text] The bloody al-Ahmar gang in Sanaa today repeated to 
fail in its aggressive attempts on the various fronts. Our air, 
ground and naval forces have been able to repel and foil these 
attempts and to rout the hostile forces, inflicting on them 
heavy losses of life and material. On the Karish-Tawr al-Baha 
axis, our forces were able to shoot down two enemy aircraft and 
destroy four Katyusha rocket launching vehicles. On this front 
the enemy lost dozens of officers and men, including a 
lieutenant colonel and a major. In a hysterical attempt, two 
enemy aircraft tried to bomb the Aden refinery, but our air 
defenses foiled them. One of the aircraft released its 
destructive load over one of the government schools in 
al-Burayqah, wounding six women and children living near the 
school. In the Abyan-Shabwah axis our forces continued 
delivering crushing blows on the invading enemy forces, 
compelling them to withdraw and return to where they had come 
from. God is great. 

</TEXT>

