Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0206110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Sanaa, an authoritative source has said that the 
Yemeni Government will hold an extraordinary meeting today in 
the wake of the resolution issued by the United Nations Security 
Council, which calls for a cease-fire in Yemen. The same source 
added that a scheduled news conference today has been postponed 
due to the convening of the emergency meeting of the Council of 
Ministers in which Planning Minister 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani 
will announce Sanaa's stand on the Security Council resolution. 

</TEXT>

