<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa Reportedly Seizes Tanks Meant for South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa Reportedly Seizes Tanks Meant for South </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0106212694 Baghdad INA in Arabic 2050 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0106212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, 1 Jun (INA) -- An official Yemeni source has 
told INA correspondent in Sanaa that the legitimate Yemeni 
forces have seized 80 tanks which were sent from Saudi Arabia to 
the secessionists in Aden. 
  The source said that Saudi Arabia moved these tanks via the 
al-'Abr border area into Hadhramaut Governotate three days ago. 
  The source added that Yemeni tribes in Shabwah Governorate 
and Hadhramaut Governorate seized the tanks when those who were 
transporting them hinted that they were representatives of 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid. 
  The source explained that as a result, Yemeni President 
Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih contacted Saudi King 
Fahd by telephone and informed him that he had received the 
consignment of tanks sent to the secessionists. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

