<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council Approves Exploitation of Hulaywah Oil Field </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council Approves Exploitation of Hulaywah Oil Field </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0106141694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0106141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Higher Council for Oil, Economic, and Investment 
Affairs held a meeting today under Acting Prime Minister Dr. 
Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar. It discussed a number of topics on 
its agenda and approved a decision to begin the best and 
quickest exploitation of the Hulaywah oil field in the Jannah 
sector. 
  The Council instructed the Ministry of Oil and Mineral 
Resources to take the necessary measures to guarantee the best 
revenues to serve the national economy. 
  The Council also discussed a number of reports submitted by 
the Finance Ministry, the Central Bank, and the Ministry of Oil 
and Mineral Resources, and took the necessary measures on them. 

</TEXT>

