<H3> <TI>   League Estimates 50,000 Killed, $10 Billion in Damages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    League Estimates 50,000 Killed, $10 Billion in Damages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0206113694 Al-Dammam AL-YAWM in Arabic 30 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0206113694 </F>
<F P=104>  Al-Dammam AL-YAWM </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Falih al-Saghir and Sa'ud al-Rayyis from Cairo] </F>
  [Excerpt] An Arab League official has said that human 
losses in 25 days of fierce fighting in Yemen have exceeded more 
than 50,000 killed from both sides. 
  In a statement to AL-YAWM, Tal'at Hamid, the League's media 
adviser, said that the material damage for the same period has 
exceeded $10 billion. He said the Yemeni infrastructure has 
also been damaged. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

