<H3> <TI>   BJP Criticizes Wisner Comments on Missile Tests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    BJP Criticizes Wisner Comments on Missile Tests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2905074794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2905074794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The BJP [Bharatiya Janata Party] has reiterated 
that the country should be firm in its stand on the Prithvi 
missile test. The party spokesman, Mr. K.L. Sharma, said in New 
Delhi today that there should be no question of shelving the 
test. Referring to some reported remarks by the U.S. 
ambassador-designate to India, Mr. Frank Wisner, Mr. Sharma 
accused the United States of adopting double standards. He said 
while the American Government helped Britain in carrying out its 
Trident missile test, it is opposing India's Prithvi tests. 

</TEXT>

