<F P=102>   JN0106162594 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 1 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0106162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In his office at noon today, Dr. 'Abd-al-Razzq 
al-Nusur, minister of public works and housing, received Dr. 
Zakariya al-Agha, member of the Palestinian National Authority 
[PNA] for housing. The ministry's director general and the 
director general of the Housing and Urban Development 
Corporation also attended the meeting. 
  Dr. al-Nusur said after the session that talks covered the 
question of housing in the self-rule areas. He indicated that 
the two sides will exchange views and technical expertise in the 
best interests of the two brotherly peoples. The Ministry of 
Public Works and Housing, al-Nusur noted, is placing all its 
technical expertise in institution building at the disposal of 
the Palestinians. The sides agreed that Jordanian contractors 
will receive preferential treatment in the self-rule areas. 

