<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier, ROK Envoy Discuss Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Premier, ROK Envoy Discuss Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Process 

<F P=102>   JN3005163494 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1100 GMT 
30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN3005163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali received 
at his office today Pak Su-chol, special envoy of the [ROK] 
president. They discussed relations between the two friendly 
countries, particularly in economic, technical, and 
technological areas, as well as ways of promoting bilateral 
cooperation. 
  During the meeting, Pak praised the democratic experiment in 
Jordan, as well as Jordan's effective role in supporting the 
peace process. The meeting was attended by Dr. Fawwaz 
Abu-al-Ghanam, acting minister of state for foreign affairs, and 
the ROK ambassador in Amman. 

