<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Salah Djebaili, director of Bab Ezzouar university 
who was assassinated 31 May, is to be buried today in his home 
town of Khenchela. Teachers and students had a last look at the 
deceased whose coffin was displayed yesterday evening in the 
university's main hall. 
  The National Association of Professors and Lecturers called 
on all teachers and employees in all universities to stop work 
yesterday and today. University employees and teachers were 
also called on to meet at Bab Ezzouar university at 1000 next 
Saturday to organize a march at the university campus. 

