<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Revolutionary Committees Movement Seminar Opens </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Revolutionary Committees Movement Seminar Opens </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3005203094 Tripoli Libyan Television Network in Arabic 
1930 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli Libyan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The 16th regional seminar of the revolutionary 
committees movement began this afternoon under the theme: For 
revolutionary tasks of defiance and confrontation. The seminar 
is being held from 30 May to 1 June. The agenda consists of 
three topics: the local topic, the pan-Arab topic, and the 
international topic. 
  The local topic is focussed on work for further improving 
production capacity, practicing self-reliance, and fortifying 
the coast. The pan-Arab topic consists of boosting the morale 
of the Arab masses, exposing the aims of colonialism, sticking 
to the pan-Arab spirit, working for destroying the artificial 
borders, and forging alliance with the active forces in the Arab 
homeland. As for the international topic, it consists in 
working for broadening the international front, forging alliance 
with the small peoples which struggle for their freedom, and 
standing with the peoples that love peace based on justice and 
respect of freedom, sovereignty, and the options of peoples. 
  The meeting of the 16th seminar of the revolutionary 
committees movement comes at a time when the Arab Libyan people 
have declared their historic resolution of defiance and 
preparedness for confrontation, as shown by the great defiance 
manifestations in which the masses took to the streets to 
receive the brother of the revolution everywhere in the Arab 
Libyan territory. 

</TEXT>

