<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Explains Expulsion of British Diplomat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Explains Expulsion of British Diplomat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106174394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for our country's Foreign Ministry 
announced today that the first secretary -- the second-ranking 
official of the British Embassy in Tehran -- must leave Iran 
within a month because of actions and behavior contrary to 
diplomatic principles and contact with terrorist groups opposed 
to the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  Denying a claim by the British Foreign Office on the 
distribution of forged documents by an Iranian diplomat 
regarding British activities and stance on Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
he said: British policies on events in Bosnian-Herzegovina are 
so obvious that there is no need to divulge them to 
international public opinion and the world's Muslims. 
  He added: British Foreign Office Minister Douglas Hogg's 
views and the raising of groundless allegations against the 
Islamic Republic of Iran come at a time when known international 
terrorists -- such as the Hypocrites [Mojahedin Khalq 
Organization] -- while being active in Britain, make use of that 
country's facilities and resources for the propagation of 
terrorism. 
  Concluding, the Foreign Ministry spokesman said: It is a 
source of great regret that Britain embarked on installing 
listening devices in the Islamic Republic of Iran's Embassy 
contrary to international law, and in response to its illegal 
act resorts to the reiteration of its futile allegations against 
Iran. 

</TEXT>

