<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-106 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  30 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Speaker Calls For Healing Arab Rift </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Speaker Calls For Healing Arab Rift </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3005155094 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1445 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3005155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 30 May (INA)--National Assembly Speaker 
Sa'di Mahdi Salih has called for healing the rift among the Arab 
nation's ranks through a positive and unified Arab position 
based on cooperation and developing the mutual fraternal 
interests of all sides. 
  During a National Assembly session here today, he expressed 
Iraq's readiness to develop this position to put the Arab house 
in order in the interest of the Arab and Islamic nations. 
  The National Assembly speaker reviewed the situation in the 
Arab and international arenas, as well as developments in light 
of the U.S. statements on the continuation of the embargo and 
the postponement of lifting it in violation of the desire of the 
international community, particularly the UN Security Council 
itself. 
  He said that the increasing world calls for lifting the 
embargo indicate all countries' desire to restore relations with 
Iraq to their previous level and to establish economic and trade 
relations in a way that will achieve their interests in this 
important region of the world. 
  Sa'di Mahdi Salih praised the international efforts to this 
effect, and said that the calls by France, Russia, China, 
Brazil, Spain, Pakistan, Nigeria, and other states constitute a 
positive stand toward the Iraqi people. He expressed the hope 
that these efforts will bear fruit in the interest of our people 
and nation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

