<H3> <TI>   MIO Unit Produces Rubber Products for Industry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MIO Unit Produces Rubber Products for Industry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN3005194394 Baghdad BABIL in Arabic 18 May 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> JN3005194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad BABIL </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jabin Bin-Hayyan Establishment, one of the units of 
the Military Industrialization Organization [MIO], has produced 
millions of rubber pieces and parts for several industrial firms 
in Iraq as its contribution toward beating the unfair blockade. 
  The director general of the establishment said these pieces 
have been sold to the General Leather Industries Establishment 
for use in the production of bags. He also said that large 
quantities of plastic containers have been sold to the General 
Medicines and Medical Equipment Company. 
  The director general added that millions of other rubber 
pieces have been sold to the Oil Ministry for use in repairing 
and maintaining gas cylinder valves, which used to be imported 
with hard currencies. He said that large quantities of school 
rulers of different sizes were sold to the Ministry of 
Education. He affirmed that Establishment teams have succeeded 
for the first time in manufacturing and producing rubber lids 
for oil tanks belonging to the Oil Ministry according to high 
standard specifications to meet the ministry's needs. 

</TEXT>

