<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Receives U.S. Senate Delegation in Tunis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Receives U.S. Senate Delegation in Tunis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106190694 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 1 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning, the brother President 'Arafat received 
a U.S. Senate delegation, in the presence of the U.S. Ambassador 
to Tunisia Mr. John McCarthy. The delegation comprises Senator 
Paul Simon, Senator Russel Fengold, and Senator Harry Reid. At 
the meeting, they reviewed the latest developments of the peace 
process and the stages of implementation of the self-rule 
agreement in Gaza and Jericho, as well as the importance of the 
donor countries meeting their commitments to bolster the 
Palestinian National Authority. 
  During the meeting, brother 'Arafat entrusted the U.S. 
Senate 
delegation with a letter for U.S. President Bill Clinton on the 
implementation of the Declaration of Principles agreement signed 
in Washington last September in the interest of the peace 
process in the Middle East. The meeting stressed the 
strengthening of bilateral relations between the U.S. Senate and 
the U.S. Congress and the PLO in the interest of the U.S. and 
Palestinian peoples, and in the service of a just peace. 
  The meting was attended by brothers: Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, 
member of the PLO Executive Committee and 'Abd-al-Latif 
Abu-Hijlah, director-general of the PLO Political Department. 

