<H4>    Al-Sahhaf, Cuba's Robaina Meet </H4>

<F P=102> JN3005180694 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1650 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN3005180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 30 May (INA) -- [Iraqi] Foreign Minister 
Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf met here today with Cuban Foreign 
Minister Roberto Robaina. 
  The foreign minister briefed his Cuban counterpart on the 
recent positive developments and new atmosphere at the UN 
Security Council in favor of Iraq, represented by the majority 
calling for lifting the embargo clamped on Iraq after Iraq has 
fulfilled its obligations toward UN Security Council Resolution 
687. 
  The minister stressed the importance of maintaining the 
spirit and essence of the non-aligned states' principles so as 
to reinforce their vital interests and entrench their 
independence. 
  Foreign Minister Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf also briefed the 
Cuban foreign minister on the Iraqis' achievements in the field 
of reconstructing their country and safeguarding its national 
security despite the unjust economic embargo imposed on Iraq. 
  The INA correspondent in Cairo cited the Cuban foreign 
minister as reiterating his country's support for Iraq's 
persistent efforts to lift the embargo, and its solidarity with 
the Iraqi people. 
  Al-Sahhaf and Robaina stressed the importance of promoting 
cooperation between the two friendly countries in the interest 
of their peoples. 
  Dr. Nabil Najm, Iraq's permanent representative to the Arab 
League, attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

