<F P=100> EGYPT </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Muslim Militant' Shoots Policeman in South </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Muslim Militant' Shoots Policeman in South </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0206054694 Paris AFP in English 2103 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206054694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, Egypt, June 1 (AFP)--A suspected Muslim 
militant shot and seriously wounded a policeman in southern 
Egypt late Wednesday, a source close to the security services 
said. 
  Salim Muhammad, a railway policeman, was in charge of 
security on the Cairo to Aswan train when he was shot as it left 
the station in Abu Mawas, in the al-Minya Province in Upper 
Egypt, 270 kilometres (167 miles) south of Cairo. 
  Security services launched a manhunt, after his attacker 
fled 
the scene, the source added. 
  Asyut is a stronghold for militants who have waged a 
two-year 
campaign to topple the secular government of President Husni 
Mubarak, which has left more than 400 dead, including policemen. 
  But until recently al-Minya had not witnessed many clashes 
between security forces and militants. 

</TEXT>

