<F P=106> [Report by Sana' al-Imam in Damascus] </F>
  [Text] Syrian Information Minister Dr. Muhammad Salman has 
asserted that the recent escalation of Israeli attacks on 
Lebanon is part of Israel's policy of organized state terrorism 
against Lebanon's sovereignty. 
  In an exclusive statement to Radio Monte Carlo, Dr. Salman 
said the timing of these attacks is part of Israel's continued 
attempts to undermine the peace process and obstruct U.S. 
efforts to end the stalemate in the peace talks, which were 
launched in accordance with the Madrid frame of reference. He 
noted that the cause of the stalemate is Israel's hard-line 
approach that rejects full withdrawal from the occupied Arab 
territories in return for full peace. 

</TEXT>

