<H4>    Al-Sahhaf Meets Pakistani Counterpart </H4>

<F P=102> JN0206175994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1405 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0206175994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 Jun (INA) -- [Iraqi] Foreign Minister 
Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf, head of the Iraqi delegation to the 
nonaligned conference in Cairo, met in Cairo today with 
Pakistani Foreign Minister Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali. 
  During the meeting, Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf briefed his 
Pakistani counterpart on the developments in the relationship 
between Iraq and the UN Special Commission following the recent 
review of the Security Council on lifting the blockade on Iraq. 
The review showed clearly Iraq's full cooperation with the 
United Nations and its Special Commission and the need to lift 
the Iraq blockade in accordance with Paragraph 22 of Resolution 
687. 
  The Pakistani foreign minister stressed his country's 
position toward lifting the Iraq blockade, which is in harmony 
with the progress that Iraq has made and Iraq's positive 
response to the efforts of the United Nations and the Special 
Commission. 
  The two sides assessed the performance of the nonaligned 
conference over the past two days and the dialogues that called 
for reviving the role of the Nonaligned Movement in light of the 
current world developments. The two sides had identical views. 

</TEXT>

