<H3> <TI>   NAM Foreign Ministers' Conference Ends in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NAM Foreign Ministers' Conference Ends in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Libya's al-Muntasir on Forced Yemeni Unity </H4>

<F P=102> NC0206122494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1135 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 Jun (MENA) -- In a statement today, 'Umar 
al-Muntasir, Libyan secretary of the General People's Committee 
for Foreign Liaison and International Cooperation -- foreign 
minister -- said that "Libya is against secession in Yemen no 
matter what the price." He said that Libya supports "imposing 
unity by the force of arms." 
  Responding to a question on his opinion should the price for 
forced unity be 50,000 dead, al-Muntasir said: "We support it 
even if the price were to be 100,000 dead; we are unity crazy." 
It is worth noting that al-Muntasir is participating in the 
Nonaligned Movement Conference currently being held in Cairo. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

