<H3> <TI>   'Abd-al-Majid: Nonaligned Ministers Support Libya </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Abd-al-Majid: Nonaligned Ministers Support Libya </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0206191094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1452 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 Jun (MENA) -- Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid today received 'Umar al-Muntasir, 
secretary of the Libyan General People's Committee for Foreign 
Liaison "foreign minister." 
  After the meeting, al-Muntasir said they discussed the 
Libyan-Western dispute and events in the Arab world, 
particularly the Yemeni crisis and the Arab and international 
efforts to end the fighting in that country. 
  Al-Muntasir added that Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid informed him that 
the nonaligned foreign ministers with whom he met on the 
sidelines of the nonaligned conference voiced support for 
Libya's stance on its dispute with the West, particularly as 
Libya has been responsive to all international demands. 
  'Abd-al-Majid said the Arab League wishes to solve the 
Libyan-Western dispute in an internationally legal framework 
while at the same time safeguarding Libyan sovereignty. 

</TEXT>

