<H3> <TI>   Doctors Confine 'Arafat to Bed, Order `Total Rest' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Doctors Confine 'Arafat to Bed, Order `Total Rest' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Beirut Reports `Serious Deterioration' </H4>

<F P=102> NC0206164194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1625 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here is a report from the news desk: 
  Press reports a short while ago said that PLO Chairman Yasir 
'Arafat is suffering from a serious deterioration in his health 
condition that might require moving him from Tunis. He is 
expected to be taken to the royal hospital [King Husayn's 
medical center in Amman] this evening or tomorrow. 
  Reports circulating among Palestinian leaders this morning 
indicated that 'Arafat's health has entered a serious stage. 
Denying this, Mrs. 'Arafat said that 'Arafat was suffering from 
bronchitis that forced him to stay in bed. 

</TEXT>

