<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Reacts to Rabin's Statements on Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Reacts to Rabin's Statements on Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0306061594 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 2 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0306061594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a letter addressed to the Nonaligned Movement 
conference convening in Cairo, brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 
'Arafat], president of the state of Palestine and chairman of 
the PLO Executive Committee, has said that the statements made 
by Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin on Jerusalem cast doubt 
on Israel's willingness to comply with the self-rule accords 
signed with the PLO. 
  Brother President Abu-'Ammar said: The prime minister of the 
Israeli entity made statements in which he said Jerusalem is the 
united capital of Israel forever. Abu-'Ammar added that these 
statements are a violation of the agreement signed in Washington 
on 13 September, particularly with regard to Jerusalem. He said 
that these statements call into question the willingness of 
Israel and its leaders to comply with signed agreements. He 
noted that the Declaration of Principles on the self-rule 
stipulates that the final status of Jerusalem will be discussed 
during the last phase of talks together with the issues of 
settlements and refugees. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

