<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Contact Said Between W. Bank, Jericho Judiciaries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Contact Said Between W. Bank, Jericho Judiciaries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0206111994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 2 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0206111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asad Mubarak, the general prosecutor of the local 
judicial system in Judaea and Samaria, has said that ever since 
the autonomy was established in Jericho, there has been no 
contact between his judicial system and that of Jericho. He 
noted that the Palestinian Authority had appointed a new 
judicial system in Jericho consisting of a prosecutor, a judge, 
and administrative staffers. 
  Our correspondent Mira Amsalem reports that Justice Minister 
David Liba'i heard Mubarak's remarks during a tour of the court 
system in Ramallah. In the course of the visit, Minister Liba'i 
rejected 'Arafat's demand to terminate the application of 
Israeli military laws in the territories. The justice minister 
said that the Palestinian Authority has jurisdiction in Gaza and 
Jericho only. He pointed out that according to the Israeli-PLO 
agreement, the Palestinian Authority does not have to extradite 
murderers and terrorists to Israel. 

</TEXT>

