<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Rejects Participation in Self-Rule </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Rejects Participation in Self-Rule </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0206192494 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1630 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0206192494 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by "a responsible source" within Hamas] </F>
  [Text] We in the Hamas Movement have heard the statements 
of 'Abbas Zaki, in which he alleged that the Hamas Movement has 
agreed, in principle, to take part in what he called the 
Palestinian Authority. 
  We state that these statements contain no truth whatsoever, 
are completely fabricated, and are designed to confuse the 
position of the Hamas Movement, which strongly rejects the 
infamous Cairo agreement. 
  The source added: The Hamas Movement reiterates its 
rejection of participation, in any form, in the authority of the 
feeble self-rule, and that no agreement was reached to hold any 
meetings with Fatah. Moreover, 'Abbas Zaki's claim that there 
is a draft covenant of honor between Fatah and the Alliance of 
Palestinian Forces has no truth and is designed to enhance the 
ugly image of self-rule and 'Arafat's leadership following the 
signing of the agreement of relinquishment in Cairo. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

