<H3> <TI>   Irrigation Experts Denied Entry to Sudan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Irrigation Experts Denied Entry to Sudan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0206202394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1608 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206202394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 Jun (MENA)--Two Egyptian experts returned 
to Cairo from Khartoum today after the Sudanese authorities 
refused, without giving a reason, to let them enter Sudan. 
  Engineer Muhammad Amin Muhammadayn, former Irrigation 
Ministry under secretary and technical adviser to the Nile Water 
Authority; and Dr. Muhammad Jasir, also a former Irrigation 
Ministry under secretary and currently a professor at the 
Institute of River Silt and Hydrology, left for Khartoum aboard 
an Egyptian plane this morning at the Sudanese Government's 
invitation to discuss several joint cooperation projects. 
  Upon his return to Cairo, engineer Muhammadayn said that the 
Sudanese authorities refused to give any reason for banning him 
and his colleague from entering the country. He said the 
Sudanese told him they will explain the reasons to Egyptian 
Public Works and Water Resources Minister 'Abd-al-Hadi Radi. 

</TEXT>

