<H3> <TI>   Police Seize Cassettes Advocating `Extremism' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Seize Cassettes Advocating `Extremism' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0206201394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1612 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 Jun (MENA)--Cairo's Security Directorate 
has carried out extensive raids in various areas of Cairo to 
surround and arrest the vendors and duplicators of unlicensed 
cassettes which contain recordings advocating religious and 
intellectual extremism. 
  The raids were ordered by Major General Mansur 'Isawi, 
assistant interior minister and Cairo security director. He 
issued instructions to confiscate the books and cassettes sold 
without proper licensing and ordered the arrest of the vendors. 
  Interior Minister Hasan al-Alfi recently issued strict 
orders 
to surround and arrest individuals who trade books and cassette 
advocating religious extremism. This act comes during an 
overall campaign to protect society by seizing extremists and 
the advocates of harmful ideas. 

</TEXT>

