<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Reacts to Israeli Raid on Hizballah Camp </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Reacts to Israeli Raid on Hizballah Camp </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    UN Security Council Meeting Sought </H4>

<F P=102> NC0206113894 Paris AFP in English 1115 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, June 2 (AFP)--Lebanon called for an urgent 
meeting of the UN Security Council after an Israeli air raid on 
a Hizballah training camp killed at least 45 people near the 
border with Syria. 
  Defence Minister Muhsin Dallul said the decision was taken 
at 
a meeting of the Supreme Defence Council, which groups the 
president, prime minister, defence minister and Army chief. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

