<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hizballah Promises Retribution for Assault </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hizballah Promises Retribution for Assault </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Group To Fight `on All Fronts' </H4>

<F P=102> NC0206152394 Paris AFP in English 1438 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, June 2 (AFP) -- The Iranian-backed Hizballah 
vowed to fight the Jewish state "on all fronts" after Israeli 
warplanes killed at least 45 guerrillas in a devastating raid on 
Thursday. 
  "From now on the battle with Israel is open on all fronts," 
Hizballah spiritual leader, Shaykh Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah, 
said in a statement. 
  "It's the biggest challenge ever. Moslems, the mujahidin and 
the oppressed have decided there is no place for Israel among 
us. The forces of world oppression will no longer have a say in 
our region," Fadlallah said. 
  "Israel and the forces of world oppression can win several 
rounds but satans big or small trying to devour us will not 
frighten us," he added. 
  Fadlallah described the United States as a "wolf which 
devours man, peace and life." 
  "We know that every shell and every Israeli warplane is in 
fact an American shell and an American warplane," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-35770 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes107_n_94015" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-107 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hizballah Promises Retribution for Assault </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hizballah Promises Retribution for Assault </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Fadlallah, Others React </H4>

<F P=102> NC0206164994 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1600 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Shaykh Muhammad Mahdi Shams al-Din has affirmed 
that despite the occupation enemy's spiteful methods and 
aggression, the resistance will continue to forge ahead with its 
confrontation of the occupation. He urged those in charge of 
the international order to end the Israeli occupation of Lebanon. 
  Acting Mufti Shaykh Muhammad Rashid Qabbani has urged the 
Arabs and the world to put an end to the Jewish acts of 
belligerence, which will trigger further conflicts and a state 
of instability in this world. [passage omitted] 
  'Allamah Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah said: We decided that 
there is no place for Israel among us. The battle [against 
Israel] will be as wide as the world so that the usurpers will 
leave our land. 
  Fadlallah criticized the United States, describing it as the 
wolf that devours man, peace, and life. Fadlallah held the 
United States responsible for the Israeli attacks. 
  Hizballah Secretary General Hasan Nasrallah stressed the 
determination to continue struggle and jihad. 

</TEXT>

