<H3> <TI>   Arab League Welcomes UNSC Resolution on Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab League Welcomes UNSC Resolution on Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0206145994 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0206145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Arab League today declared its backing for the 
UN Security Council [UNSC] resolution that calls for an 
immediate cease-fire in Yemen, for solving inter-Yemeni disputes 
peacefully, and for restoring peace and stability in that 
country. 
  The League said that Yemeni unity, which represents national 
interests and pan-Arab achievements, must be preserved. It 
announced, however, that unity cannot be imposed by force. 
  The League issued a new appeal to the Yemeni parties to 
hasten to end the tragedy in their country, as the victims are 
none other than the sons of the fraternal Yemeni people. 

</TEXT>

