<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Overflights, Shelling Continue in South </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    One Civilian Reported Killed </H4>

<F P=102> NC0206163594 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1610 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0206163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The latest security reports from the south say that 
areas in al-Nabatiyah al-Fawqa, the eastern hills of Kafr Rumman 
village, the outskirts of the abandoned Lebanese Army barracks 
in al-Nabatiyah, al-Wadi al-Akhdar, 'Ayn Bu Siwar, and Jarju' 
villages are coming under violent Israeli artillery bombardment 
from the occupation troops' posts in al-Zaffat. Citizen 'Imad 
'Abd-al-Hasan Hallal, who chanced to be driving by, was killed 
and two others riding in the same car were wounded. In the 
meantime, Israeli warplanes have conducted low altitude flights 
and carried out mock raids over al-Nabatiyah and Iqlim al-Tuffah 
areas. More in this dispatch from National News Agency's 
correspondent Muhammad Ruba'i: 
  [Begin recording] Tension reigns in the south, particularly 
in areas adjacent to the occupied border belt, and the 
resistance fighters are on the alert. Security sources have 
told us that at 1515 a rocket fell on the Yarin position in the 
central sector, where the occupation troops and their agents are 
posted. A number of personnel manning the position were 
injured. For its part, the enemy has placed its troops on alert 
in anticipation of any attack by the resistance fighters in 
response to its air raids. 
  We just received word that the enemy brought a number of 
vehicles and long-range guns into the positions and hills 
overlooking the central and Western sectors. Three 155-mm 
artillery shells have fallen on the outskirts of Kafra village, 
in the central sector, near the village school. Since 1630, 
enemy aircraft have been flying at low-altitude over the south. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

