<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chadian President Deby, Delegation Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chadian President Deby, Delegation Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Al-Qadhdhafi Urges France To Leave Chad </H4>

<F P=102> LD0506152794 Tripoli JANA in Arabic 1100 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0506152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli JANA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Remarks by Libyan leader Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi at ceremony </F>
presenting award to Chadian President Idriss Deby in Tripoli on 
4 June] 
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Since when has France defended 
freedom in Africa? France is a mortal enemy to the African 
peoples. It is the power that colonized and destroyed it, 
exploited its wealth, and despised its people. It is still 
spreading its domination over Africa by military force, and has 
not recognized the independence of the African states, including 
Chad. It considers them its colonies and works toward creating 
an international status before the United States and in Europe 
via its domination of the African continent. It has created for 
that purpose the traditional annual Francophone summit. This 
imperialist policy is exposed and condemned by the African 
peoples. What justification does France have to keep its forces 
in Chad after the end of the border dispute between Libya and 
Chad? It used to claim that there was an occupied Chadian 
territory and that there was a border dispute to keep its 
military forces to defend Chad. What will France say after this 
dispute comes to an end? How will it justify its presence in 
Chad after today? Certainly, there is no justification, except 
that it wants to occupy Chadian territory and wants Chad to 
remain its colony; otherwise it should go back to where it came 
from. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

