<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brotherhood Leader Interrogated </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Brotherhood Leader Interrogated </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0506184894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1805 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0506184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 5 Jun (MENA)--The northern al-Jizah 
Prosecution Office today interrogated Muslim Brotherhood General 
Guide Hamid Abu-al-Nasr over leaflets that were distributed 
after the 'Id al- Adha prayers. These leaflets, which bore the 
signature of Hamid Abu-al-Nasr, advocated views and terms 
opposed to the regime. Public attorney counselor Muhammad 
'Arafah confronted Abu-al-Nasr with these leaflets. Abu-al-Nasr 
stated that they indeed were issued by him. The Prosecution 
Office decided to complete interrogation with him tomorrow 
morning, 6 June. 
  The security authorities arrested four youths who were 
distributing leaflets bearing the signature of the Muslim 
Brotherhood General Guide Hamid Abu-al-Nasr. They were referred 
to the Prosecution Office which ordered them put in jail pending 
further interrogation. The Prosecution Office decided to summon 
Abu-al-Nasir to hear his testimony. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

