<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Source' Denies Recent Arms Supply to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source' Denies Recent Arms Supply to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0406181694 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0406181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source has stated that Egypt has not 
supplied the Government of Rwanda with any weapons or ammunition 
since the outbreak of the conflict in Rwanda. No contracts for 
the supply of weapons or ammunition have been concluded since 
the start of the Rwandan conflict. Egypt has suspended the 
delivery of weapons contracted prior to the outbreak of the 
conflict in Rwanda, the source added. 
  The source made this statement to comment on reports 
broadcast by the Rwandan Front's radio that Egypt has recently 
sold 33 tons of weapons worth $765,000 to the Government of 
Rwanda. The responsible source concluded his comment by saying 
that what has been delivered under earlier contracts preceded 
the outbreak of the conflict and was part a commercial deal 
concluded with Rwanda, similar what has been done with other 
countries. The implementation of the remainder of the contract 
was suspended immediately after the outbreak of the internal 
conflict in Rwanda. The source added that Egypt is eager to 
stop the bloodshed in Rwanda and halt anything that may subject 
the Rwandan people to further destruction. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

