<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir Sends Message to Sanaa Leadership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bashir Sends Message to Sanaa Leadership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0506191594 Khartoum SUNA in English 1725 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA0506191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 5 June (SUNA) -- The president of Yemen, 
General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, received Saturday [4 June] a 
message from his brother General 'Umar al-Bashir the president 
of the Republic, which was handed to him by the minister of 
culture and information 'Abd-al-Basit Sabdarat. Sabdarat who 
returned here from Sanaa on Saturday stated to SUNA that the 
message was in reply of a message sent to al-Bashir by Salih, 
which was handed to him by the Yemeni president's envoy Yahya 
Husayn al-Arashi, who visited Khartoum recently. 
  He also said the message affirmed Sudan's stance toward 
Yemen 
and its concern with Yemen unity, besides ceasefire in Yemen to 
stop the bloodshed there. 

