<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Egypt's Musa Confers With Officials on Accord, Funds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egypt's Musa Confers With Officials on Accord, Funds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0606091894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0835 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0606091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 6 Jun (MENA) -- Last night Egyptian Foreign 
Minister 'Amr Musa received Mahmud 'Abbas, alias Abu-Mazin, PLO 
Executive Committee member; and Ahmad Quray', minister of 
economy and trade for the Palestinian National Authority. They 
reviewed the Palestinian-Israeli peace process and the steps 
taken so far by the PLO to implement the Palestinian self-rule 
agreement in Gaza and Jericho signed in Cairo on 4 May. 
  Musa and the Palestinian officials also discussed the 
difficulties and obstacles facing the completion of the 
implementation of the agreement and the return of PLO Chairman 
Yasir 'Arafat and the members of the Palestinian leadership to 
Jericho and Gaza. The difficulties and obstacles are 
represented by the lack of necessary funds for the Palestinian 
National Authority. So far the Authority has not received the 
funds promised by donor countries. 

</TEXT>

