<H3> <TI>   190 Palestinian Officers, NCO's Cross Into Gaza </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    190 Palestinian Officers, NCO's Cross Into Gaza </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0506143294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1335 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0506143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Al-'Arish, 5 Jun (MENA) -- A group of 190 
Palestinian officers and noncommissioned officers arriving from 
the Palestinian headquarters in Tunis passed through the Rafah 
crossing-point today. Major General 'Abd-al-Raziq al-Mahayidah, 
commander of the Palestinian forces in Rafah, said that the 
group includes personnel from the various specialized police 
agencies. He said that this group will start work and deploy in 
the self-rule areas to augment the Palestinian police force in 
Gaza and Jericho. 

</TEXT>

