<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Radio Reports Departure of Staff for Gaza </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Radio Reports Departure of Staff for Gaza </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0406202494 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 4 
Jun 94p </F>

<F P=103> JN0406202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] One hundred fifty-eight PLO officers and staff last 
night flew out from Tunis aboard a special Tunisian plane 
chartered by Saudi Arabia to Egypt, their last stop before they 
proceed to the Gaza Strip. The group, officially regarded a 
part of the Palestine Liberation Army, is comprised of personnel 
who served over the past few years on PLO-related civic duties. 
They will travel by bus from Egypt to the crossing point in 
Rafah tomorrow, Sunday, on their way to the Gaza Strip. 

</TEXT>

