<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hashemi-Rafsanjani Pays Tribute to Khomeyni </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hashemi-Rafsanjani Pays Tribute to Khomeyni </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0406135094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0406135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on speech by President Hashemi-Rafsanjani at </F>
ceremony marking the anniversary of Imam Khomeyni's death; on 3 
June; place not given] 
  [Text] Last night, mourning ceremonies on the occasion of 
the demise of the founder of the Islamic Republic of Iran were 
held with the participation of throngs of pilgrims, mourners, 
and foreign guests at the pure mausoleum of Imam Khomeyni, may 
God's peace be upon him. 
  At these ceremonies, self-flagellation by mourning groups 
and 
participants and chanting of lamentations were carried out. 
President Hashemi-Rafsanjani addressed the gathering, 
elaborating on the dimensions of the thinking, and the political 
characteristics of Imam Khomeyni, may God be pleased with him. 
He referred to his social impact in the renaissance of Islam. 
  President Hashemi-Rafsanjani alluded to the jurisprudential, 
spiritual, moral, ethical, and inspirational aspects of the 
thinking of Imam Khomeyni--may his soul be sanctified--and 
deemed his existence a divine bounty and stressed: The Imam's 
inspiration was the quintessence of these qualities. 
  President Hashemi-Rafsanjani added: The Islamic Revolution 
of Iran led by Imam Khomeyni--may God be pleased with him--in 
the course of the history of Islam was unprecedented after the 
esteemed Prophet of Islam, may God's peace and blessings be upon 
him and his scion, in such a manner that it can be described as 
a miracle. 
  He stressed: Imam Khomeyni, may God's blessings be upon him, 
made an appropriate decision regarding the selection of the next 
leader by playing the best role at this juncture in history. If 
today we are able to ward off spewing venom, mischiefmongering, 
discord, and the destructive activities of the enemy, it is 
because we are treading the path of the revolution blazed by the 
imam behind the leader of the revolution without the slightest 
hesitation, and it is entirely due to the apt management of 
Ayatollah Khamene'i. 
  President Hashemi-Rafsanjani continued: Five years ago, at 
this same time, we were apprehensive about the future of the 
revolution. However, our trepidation was eliminated by the 
imam's guidance and with the allusions and clear indications by 
the imam regarding the future; the situation became completely 
obvious in this regard. He explained: The imam propounded the 
issue of leadership in such a manner that it would be safe from 
the treachery of the enemies who were constantly awaiting an 
opportunity to settle scores and to capitalize on the vacuum in 
the leadership. Therefore, he did not announce any individual 
choice openly. However, we found our path in the light of the 
imam's wishes and the Assembly of Experts--after these allusions 
evolved into a definite form--was able to make a suitable 
decision about the future leadership. 
  The president emphasized: During the course of the Islamic 
Revolution, we have perceived divine succor and bounties and the 
God of our imam did not stint in showering His kindness and 
blessings on the Islamic ummah. Following the demise of the 
imam, the multifaceted and comprehensive expediency and 
management continued to resolve the problems of the revolution 
in such a manner that it went on treading its path. The fear 
that had weighed on the hearts of the ever-present-on-the-scene 
ummah metamorphosed into confidence, trust, and self-reliance 
and we continued on the imam's path. 
  In another part of his speech, President Hashemi-Rafsanjani 
expressed his gratitude to Hojjat ol-Eslam val-Moslemin Seyyed 
Ahmad Khomeyni, the esteemed remembrance of the imam, for his 
services during the struggle period, and in the aftermath of the 
revolution and he also thanked the household of the imam. 
  At the conclusion of his remarks, the president said that if 
today we are able to continue down our path behind the rightful 
successor of the imam -- who is the best person imaginable to 
shoulder this responsibility, to reconstruct the country, and to 
insist on the aspirations of the imam -- it is entirely due to 
the guidance and foresight of our dear imam. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

