<H3> <TI>   Speaker Nateq-Nuri Addresses Khomeyni Mourners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Speaker Nateq-Nuri Addresses Khomeyni Mourners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306201994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0306201994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the death anniversary of His Eminence Imam 
Khomeyni, may his soul be sanctified, last night the tomb of the 
great leader was the scene of a large number of people who had 
gathered there to mourn him and to pay homage to him. 
  Speaking to the mourners, Majles Speaker Nateq-Nuri pointed 
out that five years after the death of the founder of the 
Islamic Republic, Imam Khomeyni's line and path are continuing 
strongly, he said that the secret behind the success of the 
Islamic revolution is the bond between the ummah and the supreme 
leader. He added: With all the knowledge that it has of the 
Imam, the Islamic Republic can still not fully understand the 
various aspects of his character. The Majles speaker said: It 
is a source of pride for the rule of the supreme leader and for 
the Islamic Republic to have victoriously stood up for eight 
years in front of the entire world of arrogance to defend its 
religion and homeland. 
  Later in his remarks, Nateq-Nuri stressed that our 
government 
and nation would defend the country's territorial integrity with 
its life and said: We believe that regional security is 
beneficial to all the regional countries and that irresponsible 
remarks and satanic overtures by some regional countries would 
not benefit peace and security in the region. 
  The head of the legislative branch referred to the stances 
of 
the esteemed leader in support of the Muslims and the oppressed 
of the world and said: As far as Palestine is concerned, the 
only alternative is that the Zionists leave the occupied 
territories and that the Palestinians' sovereignty be 
established over their land. 

</TEXT>

