<H3> <TI>   Hashemi-Rafsanjani Meets With Foreign Dignitaries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hashemi-Rafsanjani Meets With Foreign Dignitaries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606101994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] At a meeting with foreign dignitaries taking part 
in the ceremonies marking the fifth anniversary of the death of 
His Holiness Imam Khomeyni, may his soul be sanctified, the 
president of the Islamic Republic of Iran ['Ali Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani] stressed the need for unity among the world 
Muslims. 
  The president said: The big problem of the world of Islam is 
the lack of unity between Muslims. The Islamic Republic of Iran 
will do its best to create unity and has reached out the hand of 
unity toward all Islamic countries. 
  According to our correspondent, Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani said: 
The Islamic Republic of Iran has no intention of interfering in 
the internal affairs of any country. We hope Islamic 
governments do not interpret our advice as interference in their 
domestic affairs. 
  Referring to the fact that Islamic Iran is very serious in 
the country's construction the president said: Our dependence on 
the outside world is being reduced every day. What worries us 
today is the existence of problems in the world of Islam, such 
as in Yemen, Afghanistan, Bosnia, and Palestine. 
  Stressing that the Islamic revolution has continued on its 
course for the past 15 years without any foreign backing, he 
said the success and the historical miracle stem from the power 
of Islam and the wise leadership of the imam [Khomeyni]. 
  Criticizing certain Islamic governments for mischief-making 
against the Islamic revolution, the president said: They intend 
to divert toward Iran the opposition of world Muslims to Israel. 
That is an astonishing crime and very woeful for the Muslim 
world. 
  The president added: Public opinion in the world of Islam 
has 
been awakened. We hope that the enemies of Islam will realize 
that and cease their mischief-making. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

