<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   1 Million Refugees Return From Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    1 Million Refugees Return From Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206121694 Tehran IRNA in English 1130 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zahedan, Sistan va Baluchistan Prov., IRNA -- One 
million Afghan refugees have so far returned to their country, 
the Interior Ministry's director general in charge of foreign 
national affairs 'Ali Husseini [name as received] said here 
Thursday. 
  The return of the refugees was arranged by a tripartite 
commission comprising the governments of Iran and Afghanistan 
and the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR). 
  Preparations have been made for return home of some 300,000 
more Afghan refugees this year, Husseini told IRNA. 
  Husseini said that according to the policies of the Islamic 
Republic, those Afghan refugees who have received identification 
cards may stay in Iran as long as they wish. 
  The commission has given those Afghans in Iran illegally 
until July 1 to leave the country, he said. 

</TEXT>

