<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unit Leaves To Join Bosnian Peacekeeping Force </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unit Leaves To Join Bosnian Peacekeeping Force </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0406144494 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0406144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The second group of 300 Pakistani troops left 
Lahore this morning for the Slovak Republic for onward 
deployment in Bosnia. The troops will form part of the United 
Nations peacekeeping mission in the war-torn Muslim country. 
The third group of troops is expected to leave within a 
fortnight. These groups are scheduled to undergo requisite 
training in the Slovak Republic for a period of two weeks and 
then fly to Bosnia to take their peacekeeping duties under the 
auspices of the United Nations. The remaining troops of the main 
body will be flown directly to Bosnia under a phased program 
expected to be completed by the end of July this year. At 
Lahore Airport, they were seen off by senior officers of the 
Pakistan Army. 

</TEXT>

