<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bhutto `Disappointed' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bhutto `Disappointed' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0406150594 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0406150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, has said 
she is disappointed to learn that the leader of the opposition 
is unable to accept her invitation for June 5 to take him into 
confidence about the current economic situation and the measures 
needed to give economic stability to the country. In a letter 
to Mr. Nawaz Sharif, the prime minister said she had made the 
invitation in good faith and in the greater national interests. 
In her letter, she said a democratic government always works 
within constitutional framework. The last elections were the 
fairest since 1977 and its verdict has been acceptable to all. 
As regards your concerns about the NWFP [North-West Frontier 
Province] assembly and other matters, she hoped you will seek 
relief through the courts of law or other constitutional 
mechanism available. It would be best for both of us to accept 
constitutional realities which cannot be subjected to political 
pressures. In view of your inability, I have directed the 
minister for finance to hold a meeting with your representative 
tomorrow at 0500 at the Q Block for this purpose. 

</TEXT>

