<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Than 30 Arabs Wounded in Hebron Riots </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More Than 30 Arabs Wounded in Hebron Riots </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0406155094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 4 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0406155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Over 30 local residents were wounded in riots in 
Hebron today. Of these, 25 people were wounded by rubber 
bullets; they were treated and sent home. Six others were 
wounded by live gunfire: one seriously, one moderately, and 
four slightly. 
  Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that an IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] soldier who was hit by a stone suffered moderate 
injuries. Two other soldiers and a border policeman sustained 
slight injuries. 
  Our correspondent notes that an investigation into the 
incident in which a grenade was thrown at an IDF unit this 
morning has revealed that six local residents were wounded by 
shrapnel. There were no IDF casualties. 

</TEXT>

