<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Curfew Imposed on Town Center </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Curfew Imposed on Town Center </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0506115094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 5 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0506115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Border police have detained dozens of rioters and 
stone throwers in Hebron and a curfew has been imposed on the 
town center. Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that two 
explosive devices were hurled at an IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
patrol last night, but nobody was hurt. Disturbances broke out 
a short time ago in Ramallah. A soldier sustained light wounds 
from a stone and glass splinters when a military vehicle was 
stoned in the center of town. One of the soldiers opened fire to 
extricate the vehicle from the stone throwers. Border police 
forces restored order with tear gas and rubber bullets. There 
have so far been four people lightly wounded and they were 
transferred to Ramallah hospital. 
  The IDF this morning prevented a group of Jordan Rift Valley 
settlers from entering Jericho in a convoy bearing Israeli flags 
thereby protesting the fact that at the weekend the IDF 
prevented one of the settlers from passing through Jericho with 
an Israeli flag. Earlier, there was a clash between Israeli 
policemen and the demonstrators when the former tried to prevent 
Palestinian vehicles from traveling with PLO flags along roads 
in the Jordan Rift Valley. 

</TEXT>

