<F P=102>   NC0306150294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1308 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0306150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 3 Jun (MENA) -- PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat 
last night received Sten Anderson, head of the Scandinavian 
Countries Council and Sweden's former foreign minister. 
  The Palestinian News Agency WAFA said 'Arafat and Anderson 
discussed the latest developments in the Middle East peace 
process, especially the Palestinian National Authority's 
takeover of its tasks in the Palestinian land. The discussion 
also dealt with the Palestinian Authority's responsibility for 
reconstructing Palestine and the international community's 
responsibility to help in this task. 
  The Palestinian News Agency said the head of the 
Scandinavian 
Countries Council expressed his support for the Palestinian 
National Authority with all means to enable it to implement its 
tasks. 
  Informed sources here expressed their belief that announcing 
this meeting, which might have taken place in 'Arafat's home, 
aims to counter reports on the seriousness of 'Arafat's illness. 
  Informed Palestinian sources affirmed that a suite has been 
booked for 'Arafat at the Medical City in Jordan and that 
'Arafat will be moved there in the next few days for treatment 
and necessary medical tests. 
  It was announced yesterday that 'Arafat had suffered a 
severe 
ailment that kept him at home and halted his activities. 

</TEXT>

