<H3> <TI>   Peres Explains Letter to 'Arafat on Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres Explains Letter to 'Arafat on Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Letter Sent to Norwegian Minister </H4>

<F P=102> TA0506065994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0405 GMT 5 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0506065994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres returned home from 
Morocco Friday [3 June] and said Israel insists that the 
Palestinian self-rule would be in Jericho and not in Jerusalem. 
  [Begin Peres recording] I did not send any letter to Yasir 
'Arafat. I sent a letter to the Norwegian foreign minister in 
response to his letter to me. My letter was not even addressed 
top secret and contained my remarks to the Knesset. The reason 
for my action was our insistence that the Palestinian civilian 
authority be based in Jericho and not in Jerusalem. I said we 
do not want to harm the spiritual, cultural, medical 
institutions in Jerusalem, but that the authority would deal 
only with Jericho. I would like to remind you that the 
negotiations almost blew up over the Jericho issue because of 
our insistence that the autonomy's center would be in Jericho. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

