<F P=103> LD3105224094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat RTM Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] A joint communique issued by Mr. Driss Basri, 
minister of state for the interior and information, and Mr. Erik 
Jensen, the UN representative's special assistant and head of 
the voter identification commission, which was published today 
in Rabat, announced that the operation to determine the identity 
of Saharans involved in the referendum will begin on 8 June 1994 
in Laayoune. The joint communique says: 
  After a working session held on 30 May, the minister of 
interior and information and the chairman of the voter 
identification commission bring to the notice of all Saharans 
involved in the referendum that the operation to determine their 
identity will begin on 8 June 1994 in Laayoune. 
  The regulations will be displayed at the headquarters of the 
municipality and its annex as well as at the headquarters of the 
UN Mission for the Referendum in Western Sahara, as soon as they 
have been drafted. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

