<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Jordanian] Interior Minister Salamah Hammad met 
with his Iraqi counterpart Watban Ibrahim in Baghdad yesterday. 
  The IRAQI NEWS AGENCY quoted Ibrahim as hailing Jordan's 
position on Iraq during and after the Gulf war. 
  AKHIR KHABAR has learned that Hammad's visit to Baghdad 
follows several diplomatic and political contacts relating to 
Jordanian citizens in Iraq. It also learned that Hammad is 
carrying a special security file on activating security 
agreements signed previously in Amman and Baghdad. The file 
also deals with the recent increase in cases against Jordanian 
citizens. 
  AKHIR KHABAR also learned that the interior minister's talks 
in Baghdad deal with increasing bilateral coordination, and 
reaching an agreement on a mechanism to control illegal trade 
across the Jordanian-Iraqi border, especially following an 
increase in smuggling operations. 
  Hammad's visit also aims at fostering bilateral security 
coordination. 
  Observers noted that Hammad is the first official to visit 
Iraq after the latest government changes, according to which 
President Saddam Husayn assumed the post of prime minister in 
order to launch the battle to lift the siege imposed on Iraq. 

</TEXT>

