<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Warns Syria To Restrain Hizballah </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Warns Syria To Restrain Hizballah </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0206175794 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0206175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin by political </F>
correspondent Gadi Sukenik on 2 June; place not given -- 
recorded] 
  [Text] [Rabin] It is an ongoing war. Whenever there is a 
opportunity to hit the terrorist organization Hizballah without 
necessarily harming civilians, we do so, and we will continue 
doing so. They violated the understandings and responded with 
Katyusha attacks on civilian targets on Israeli soil. The fact 
that there have been no casualties or damage up to this point 
does not change the fact that they violated the understandings. 
And if they continue, we will have to respond to the violations. 
  I presented the matter to the Americans via the ambassador 
here. It was the Americans who mediated the understandings. I 
prefer that they first try to arrange something within the 
framework of the understandings with Hizballah's patrons, the 
Syrians, but if this situation continues, we will not be able to 
abide it. 
  [Sukenik] What prevented Israel from hitting that base 
before? Why today? 
  [Rabin] We chose the right time because they are not always 
there. 
  [Sukenik] Did you take into account the possibility that the 
price for attacking that base might be painful if Katyushas harm 
Israelis? 
  [Rabin] Yes, because in harming them we harm those who in 
another week or two months will operate against us. [end 
recording] 
  [Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in Hebrew on 
1700 
GMT on 2 June carries similar remarks by Prime Minister Rabin at 
an Armored Corps gathering in Latrun. Asked by correspondent 
'Imanu'el Rosen whether the air raid might harm negotiations 
with Syria, Rabin says in a recorded passage: "There is no tie 
between the political negotiations with Syria and our war 
against Hizballah. Hizballah is the one that initiates the 
attacks against the IDF [Israeli Defense Forces] and SLA [South 
Lebanese Army] in the security zone, therefore the war against 
it is not carried out by responding to an act, but through an 
ongoing war based on the understandings reached in the wake of 
Operation Accountability in July 1993."] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

