  [Text] The finance and agriculture ministers have declared 
parts of the Negev and the Galilee as drought areas. Our 
correspondent Shulamit Schmerling reports that as a result of 
the decision, farmers will be eligible for compensation. The 
Agriculture Ministry estimates that the scope of damages will 
reach a total of 10 million shekels. 

