<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNRWA Asked To Increase Refugee Services </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNRWA Asked To Increase Refugee Services </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0206180994 Amman Radio Jordan in English 1600 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0206180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali has 
received at his office the UNRWA [United Nations Relief and 
Works Agency] high commissioner and heads of delegates 
participating in the unofficial meeting of the representatives 
of the major donor countries for UNRWA and the refugees hosting 
countries currently held in Amman. 
  During the audience, the premier has underlined the 
importance of work at this stage to guarantee the continuity of 
UNRWA to work and promote its services offered to Palestinian 
refugees until a permanent and just settlement for their cause 
is reached. 
  Dr. al-Majali urged the donor countries to increase their 
donations, provide more support for UNRWA, and increase their 
contribution in its budget to enable it carry out its role. 
  The prime minister said that all refugees should receive the 
same treatment in the hosting countries without any 
discrimination as their cause is one and their basic needs are 
identical regardless of their location. 
  He urged the UNRWA to provide more services for the 
Palestinian refugees as Jordan is hosting the biggest number of 
Palestinian refugees and incurring heavy financial burdens, 
especially in the fields of health and education. 

</TEXT>

