<H3> <TI>   Journalists Protest Media `Bias' in Yemen Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Journalists Protest Media `Bias' in Yemen Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0206180594 Amman SHIHAN in Arabic 4-10 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> JN0206180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SHIHAN </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Some 61 Jordanian journalists and writers have sent 
a memorandum of protest to Information Minister Dr. Jawad 
al-'Anani against the Jordanian official media's coverage of 
Yemeni developments. 
  The memorandum said that the coverage is biased and 
contradicts the Jordanian official position and role as a 
sponsor of the accord document. This coverage will also not 
help Jordan to play a role in the future as an honest broker and 
a friend of all Yemeni forces. 
  The memorandum demanded that the official media stop showing 
bias. 

</TEXT>

