<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Regional Power Grid Tenders Due By Year's End </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Regional Power Grid Tenders Due By Year's End </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2805151294 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1100 GMT 
28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2805151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Walid 'Asfur, minister of energy and mineral 
resources, has said the tenders for the power-linkage project 
between Jordan and Egypt -- a first stage in a comprehensive 
power grid linking Jordan, Syria, Iraq, Egypt, and Turkey -- 
will be submitted before the end of this year. The project is 
expected to be finished by 1997. 
  In a statement to the Jordanian News Agency, 'Asfur said the 
ministers of energy and electricity and the heads of delegations 
of the five-way power-linkage states stressed, at the conclusion 
of their meetings in Cairo recently, the need for power linkage 
between Jordan and Egypt as a basic, first stage in the 
comprehensive linkage between the five states. 
  He noted that it was agreed to give priority in financing 
the 
project to the implementation of the first stage. The Arab Fund 
for Economic and Social Development will finance the two parts 
of the Jordanian-Egyptian linkage; the two parts of the 
Jordanian-Syrian linkage; and the Syrian part of the 
Syrian-Turkish linkage. 
  'Asfur said the next ministerial meeting of the five-way 
power-linkage states will be held in Turkey in April next year. 

</TEXT>

