<F P=102>   JN0206130294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1115 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0206130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Beirut -- According to the latest counts, 
released at noon today, 45 persons were left martyred and 85 
others injured by the treacherous, savage Israeli warplanes' 
aggression against one of Ba'labakk's suburbs in the Lebanese 
al-Biqa' Valley. Hospital sources in Ba'labakk said that the 
number of martyrs is likely to increase because of the presence 
of serious injuries among the wounded. 
  In a statement on the brutal raid, Lebanese security sources 
said that at least three Israeli helicopters took part in this 
raid, using machine guns and rockets, and that other planes were 
flying at high altitudes to protect them. Reports say that 
Lebanese Army ground defenses confronted the raiding planes and 
prevented them from staging any landing. MENA said that a 
six-plane squadron was supporting the Israeli helicopters and 
dropped heat balloons in a precautionary measure to avoid the 
Lebanese army's ground defenses. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

