<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Reports 60 Northerners Killed in Radfan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0506191094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1630 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0506191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1630 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The soldiers in the war of liberation against the 
British, and their brave young people in Radfan Province have 
sent the following cable to the chairman and members of the 
Presidential Council and the command of the Armed Forces in the 
Democratic Republic of Yemen [DRY]: We send you our warmest 
congratulations on the occasion of the declaration of the DRY, 
on behalf of our colleagues Labbuzah, Thabit Husayn al-Uqbi, and 
other strugglers in the war of liberation, and send you a 
suitable gift contained in what follows: 
  A group of fighters in the war of liberation and their brave 
youths attacked the invading enemy forces as they arrived at one 
of the remote villages in Radfan Province. A fierce battle 
ensued, lasting from 1100 on 3 June until the dawn of the 
following day. The following losses were inflicted on the enemy: 
Three military vehicles destroyed, 60 men killed, and a number 
of others wounded. One of our colleagues was martyred, while six 
others were lightly wounded. In response, the enemy proceeded 
to shell villages indiscriminately, martyring a citizen and 
wounding a number of others. We promise our political 
leadership in the DRY that we shall deal with these new 
occupiers just as we dealt with the colonialists, and shall not 
give up an inch of the territory of the DRY. This is a promise 
from strong and loyal strugglers: We shall rout the attacking 
forces, and victory will be our ally, God willing. 

</TEXT>

