<H3> <TI>   Aden Reports North Losses in Attack at al-Shu'ayb </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aden Reports North Losses in Attack at al-Shu'ayb </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0506204094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1900 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0506204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 1900 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The popular resistance in the al-Shu'ayb district 
succeeded in resisting an aggressive assault mounted by the 
enemy forces last night and today, and inflicted heavy losses on 
them. This happened when the enemy forces sent a company 
[sariyyah] from the Hamzah Brigade forward, with support from 
all forms of heavy weapons, including Katyushas. They attempted 
to occupy a number of villages in al-Shu'ayb. They carried out 
random shelling against the villages and their peaceful 
inhabitants, which led to the wounding of four citizens. 
  Popular resistance forces engaged the attackers, led by the 
fighters of the liberation war, from last night until this 
afternoon. The enemy suffered heavy losses, as 24 men were 
killed or wounded. Our forces also destroyed three military 
vehicles, along with their crews. An enemy reconnaissance 
officer was captured. The rest of the enemy forces were 
compelled to withdraw and flee in the direction of Qa'tabah. 

</TEXT>

