<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salih Briefs King Husayn on `Blatant Interference' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Briefs King Husayn on `Blatant Interference' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0606054094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0606054094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A telephone contact took place yesterday evening 
between brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, and his brother His 
Majesty King Husayn Bin-Talal, king of the sisterly Hashemite 
Kingdom of Jordan. During this telephone conversation, 
President Salih briefed King Husayn on the latest developments 
in our country in light of the signs of blatant interference in 
Yemen's affairs. 
  The brother leader president renewed his commendation of the 
lofty, principled pan-Arab stand of His Majesty King Husayn 
Bin-Talal and the brothers in Jordan and their support for our 
Yemeni people, Yemeni unity, democracy, and constitutional 
legitimacy. The president stressed that despite the challenges 
to unity imposed by the rebellious and secessionist gang, which 
sold itself to the devil, our people will defend unity being the 
great strategic objective. Our people struggled and offered 
dear sacrifices to achieve this historic national objective and 
pan-Arab gain. 
  King Husayn Bin-Talal reiterated, during the telephone 
contact, sisterly Jordan's support for unity, democracy, and 
legitimacy in our country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

