<H3> <TI>   Abyan Tribe Pledges Allegiance to Salih </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abyan Tribe Pledges Allegiance to Salih </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0506075494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0506075494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The shaykhs, notables, and sons of the Ba Kazm tribe 
in the Districts of al-Mahfid and Ahwar in the Abyan Governorate 
have issued a statement denying the reports issued by the 
secessionist remnants over their media organs regarding alleged 
and baseless support by their tribe. The statement said that 
the shaykhs and notables of the Ba Kazm tribe, who played an 
honorable role in resisting colonial rule and evil powers over 
the past 25-year rule of the secessionist gang, declare their 
adherence to unity and constitutional legitimacy. This 
reflects, the statement added, the principled positions they 
have announced in early 1991, when they met with brother 
President Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih. During that 
meeting, the statement noted, they pledged to support and defend 
unity. 
  The statement added that the treasonous, agent, and 
secessionist gang within the Yemeni Socialist Party and its 
allied hirelings, feeling that they are now in their death 
throes, are fabricating alleged and baseless cables of 
congratulations to deceive the public opinion through cheap 
tactics. They have used the name of the Ba Kazm tribe, given 
its profound influence and role, in an attempt to influence the 
positions of other tribes, forgetting that unity and Yemen are 
dearer and more chaste than all filthy money. 
  The Ba Kazm notables concluded their statement by extending 
their greetings, appreciation, and absolute allegiance to the 
symbol struggler Lt. Gen. 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, and expressing 
support for constitutional legitimacy, the leadership, and the 
governorate represented by Abyan Governor struggler 'Ali Shaykh 
'Umar, and the forces vindicating legitimacy and unity. 
  God is great. Victory and pride to unity, constitutional 
legitimacy, and Yemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

