<H3> <TI>   Al-Jifri Appeals for Halt to Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Jifri Appeals for Halt to Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WA0406234194 London MBC Television in Arabic 2100 GMT 4 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> WA0406234194 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 


    [Text] Our correspondent in Aden reported a short time ago 
that fire is illuminating Aden's sky because of missiles being 
fired by the southern forces to down northern forces' missiles. 
  The corredspondent affirmed that the vice president of the 
proclaimed Presidential Council in Aden, 'Abd-al-Rahman 
al-Jifri, contacted him a short while ago asking that an appeal 
be addressed through the MBC to the international community to 
halt the war. This comes after the northerners pounded the city 
of al-Waht 60 km from Aden. 
  Al-Jifri said the attack on al-Waht killed and wounded many 
of its residents and displaced those who survived. He appealed 
to humanitarian organizations to supply Aden with doctors and 
medical aid. 

</TEXT>

