<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   AFP on Request for Aid From Saudi Arabia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    AFP on Request for Aid From Saudi Arabia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0506180694 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 0300 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0506180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network 
in Arabic 0300 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The vice chairman of the Presidential Council, 
Brother 'Abd-al-Rahman 'Ali al-Jifri, said that what had been 
reported in the media as a statement by him to the French news 
agency, AFP -- that the Democratic Republic of Yemen would ask 
for military assistance from the brotherly Kingdom of Saudi 
Arabia -- had never happened. 
  In a statement to the Yemeni NEWS AGENCY, Aden, al-Jifri 
said 
that the Democratic Republic of Yemen had made no decision to 
ask for military intervention from any side. He stated that 
what had happened was that he had replied to a question by AFP 
on whether the Democratic Republic of Yemen would seek military 
assistance from any quarter by saying that such a decision had 
not yet been made, but that anything was possible, and that if 
we decided to demand anything, we would ask the United Nations 
to act on Resolution No. 924. 
  The vice chairman added that there was no mention in his 
reply concerning any country which held our trust and pride, 
such as our brothers in the Gulf Cooperation Council -- the 
Republic of Egypt, Syria, and the rest of Arab countries. 
  The vice chairman said that when questioned on this matter, 
the AFP correspondent denied that he had filed this statement, 
or that his agency had published this version of the story. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

